HEADWORD: Hypogastric
<hw>Hyp`o*gas"tric</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>hypogastrique</ets>. See <er>Hypogastrium</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to the hypogastrium or the
hypogastric region.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Hypogastric region</b></col>. <sd>(a)</sd> <cd>The lower
part of the abdomen.</cd> <sd>(b)</sd> <cd>An arbitrary division of the
abdomen below the umbilical and between the two iliac
regions.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hypogastrium</ent>⟦br⟧
